# SecPad v1

## English

SecPad is a temporary text editor designed for handling sensitive text such as IDs and passwords.

It is intended to be used as a local, temporary workspace to verify and copy text before pasting it into other applications.

### Features

- No save functionality
- No network functionality
- Temporary text editing
- Copy / Paste / Cut
- Font can be changed for better readability
- Text area is cleared when the application closes
- Clipboard is cleared on exit (best effort)

### Security Policy

SecPad is designed with the following principles:

- No data is stored locally
- No network communication is performed
- Text exists only during runtime
- On exit, the application clears the text area and attempts to clear the clipboard

### Notes

- This application is not a password manager
- Do not use it for long-term storage
- Clipboard clearing is performed on a best-effort basis
- Due to OS behavior or other software, clipboard history may remain

### Usage

1. Paste temporary data into SecPad
2. Verify the content visually
3. Copy only the necessary part
4. Paste it into the target application
5. Close SecPad to discard all data

### Font

You can change the font to improve readability.

This helps distinguish similar characters such as:

- 1 / I / l / |
- 0 / O
- 6 / b

